sql:
SELECT f.title, f.tagline
FROM films f
INNER JOIN sequels s ON f.film_id = s.sequel_film_id
WHERE s.film_id = (
  SELECT film_id FROM films WHERE title = 'Pirates of the Caribbean: At World''s End'
);

external_knowledge:
Endurance beyond two hours: refers to films that are longer than 120 minutes;
Dawn of the new millennium: refers to the release date of the films being after January 1, 2000;
Sequence of their debut: means the order by which the films were released, starting from the earliest to the most recent.

sql:
SELECT title
FROM films
WHERE film_id IN (SELECT film_id FROM sequels);

